Source:  Farming in the Mohaka State Forest
Author:  WRIGHT
Vol / Page:  7
Edition:
Quote:  The burn-and-graze technique most commonly used in farms such as those in the Mohaka region during the nineteenth century was developed by Archdeacon Samuel Williams and J.H.Coleman, who discovered that fern could be burnt in January when the sap was up, and that regrowth would mature in about a month.
